Your studies of trick-taking and card combinations have come a long way. We have seen some solid suits, suits in which tricks can be won via promotion, and long suits in which the small cards can win tricks.

The card combinations we studied so far have one thing in common: They all contained lots of touching cards.

When there are ^*Igaps^*N in a card combination things get more complicated...|
