ht|h|at|^^with the intention of playing the @SA should the @SK appear, and playing the @SQ otherwise, is an example of a technique that bridge players call a finesse.

There are many types of finesses in bridge and we will examine several of these in this chapter. The finesse is one of the most useful ways for a declarer to win extra tricks at bridge. It is not that easy to come up with a good general definition of the finesse, but the following is reasonable:

|cs|1|at|^-{A finesse is a play that will win an extra trick (or tricks) in a suit, provided
that a key card (or cards) is located in a particular defender's hand.}|
